\par (b) Taxis (Five Regions). It is thought very wrong that taxis are used to bring people home from dances, and for pub-crawling and shopping. 
\par 
\par (c) Business men (Four Reckons) "who come home from work to lunch in a car" and "use their cars for short distances which could be walked".
\par 
\par (d) The British army (Three Regions).
\par 
\par (e) U.S. troops (Three Regions).
\par 
\par (f) Farmers (Two Regions).
